{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC22","title":"Create macOS or Linux virtual machines","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10002-Create-macOS-or-Linux-virtual-machines","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (23 min)","isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc22\/10002"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc22-10002-create-macos-or-linux-virtual-machines"]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how you can use the Virtualization framework to quickly create virtual machines on your Mac. We‚Äôll show you how to create a virtual Mac and quickly test changes to your app in an isolated environment. We‚Äôll also explore how you can install and run full Linux distributions on Apple silicon, and share how you can take advantage of Rosetta 2 to run x86-64 Linux binaries.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization\/running_gui_linux_in_a_virtual_machine_on_a_mac","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"anchor":"The-stack-that-enables-virtualization","text":"The stack that enables virtualization","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hardware"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple silicon has special hardware that enables the virtualization of CPUs and memory","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"can run multiple OSes on top of a single SoC"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS kernel"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"software that takes advantage of the hardware"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"no need to write kernel extensions (or KEXTs)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/hypervisor","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"low-level API that lets you virtualize CPUs and memory"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"used to access the macOS kernel virtualization capabilities from your application"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"high-level API that lets you virtualize machines"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"enables the creation of virtual machines running macOS on Apple silicon, or Linux on both Apple silicon and Intel","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Virtualization-Framework","text":"Virtualization Framework","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using Virtualization framework, we‚Äôll deal with two kinds of objects:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuration objects - which define all the properties of our virtual machines"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Virtual machine objects - abstract virtual machines and how to interact with them"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"1-Configuration-objects","text":"1. Configuration objects","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"define the hardware"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"creating a configuration is like configuring a Mac on the Apple Store (how many CPUs, how much memory, what kind of devices)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"we can add a display, and we get to see the content"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"we can add a keyboard, and we can type","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"we can add a trackpad, and we can interact with the UI","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"done in code:"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["var configuration = VZVirtualMachineConfiguration()           \/\/ üëàüèª root object of all configurations","configuration.cpuCount = 4                                    \/\/ üëàüèª 4 CPUs","configuration.memorySize = (4 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024) as UInt64 \/\/ üëàüèª 4 GB of memory","configuration.storageDevices = [newBlockDevice()]             \/\/ üëàüèª one storage device","configuration.pointingDevices = [newPointingDevice()]         \/\/ üëàüèª 4 GB of memory"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"2-Virtual-machine-objects","text":"2. Virtual machine objects","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"running a virtual machine:"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["let virtualMachine = VZVirtualMachine(configuration: configuration) \/\/ üëàüèª the configuration from before","try await virtualMachine.start() \/\/ üëàüèª boot it up"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To interact with the virtual machines, we need to use other objects from the Virtualization framework","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"to show a virtual display:"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["let virtualMachineView = VZVirtualMachineView() \/\/ üëàüèª just a normal NSView","virtualMachineView.virtualMachine = virtualMachine","","... \/\/ integrate virtualMachineView in your app to see the content of the virtual machine"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Run-full-OSes-in-virtual-machines","text":"Run full OSes in virtual machines","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"macOS","text":"macOS","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Configuration","text":"Configuration","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We need to set two special properties in our configuration to make a Mac virtual machine:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a. hardware model - specifies which version of the virtual Mac we want.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"b. auxiliary storage - form of non-volatile memory used by the system","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"c. machine identifier - unique number representing the machine","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"boot loader - must be macOS boot loader","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"code":["\/\/ üëáüèª same as before","var configuration = VZVirtualMachineConfiguration()","configuration.cpuCount = 4","configuration.memorySize = (4 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024) as UInt64","configuration.storageDevices = [newBlockDevice()]","configuration.pointingDevices = [newPointingDevice()]","","\/\/ üëáüèª Platform properties","let platform = VZMacPlatformConfiguration() \/\/ üëàüèª platform object","","let hardwareModel = VZMacHardwareModel(dataRepresentation: savedHardwareModel)","platform.hardwareModel = hardwareModel! \/\/ üëàüèª hardware model","","let auxiliaryStorage = VZMacAuxiliaryStorage(contentsOf: auxiliaryStorageURL)","platform.auxiliaryStorage = auxiliaryStorage \/\/ üëàüèª auxiliary storage","","let machineIdentifier = VZMacMachineIdentifier(dataRepresentation: savedIdentifier)","platform.machineIdentifier = machineIdentifier! \/\/ üëàüèª machine identifier","","configuration.platform = platform \/\/ üëàüèª we set special properties in our configuration object","","\/\/                            üëáüèª Mac Boot loader","configuration.bootLoader = VZMacOSBootLoader()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"How-to-install-macOS-into-a-vm","text":"How to install macOS into a vm","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Three steps:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"download and restore image (we can choose which maoOS version we want to install)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"create configuration (compatible with image above)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"run installer","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"code":["\/\/ 1. get and restore image","","let restoreImage = try await VZMacOSRestoreImage.latestSupported \/\/ üëàüèª gets a restores image object for the latest stable version of macOS","\/\/ alternatively we could download from the developer portal","","try await download(restoreImage.url)","","\/\/ 2. create configuration","","let requirements = restoreImage.mostFeaturefulSupportedConfiguration","\/\/ üëÜüèª this lists us the requirements to run on the current system","","guard let requirements = requirements else {","    \/\/ No compatible configuration.","    return","}","","platform.hardwareModel = requirements.hardwareModel","","configuration.cpuCount = requirements.minimumSupportedCPUCount","configuration.memorySize = requirements.minimumSupportedMemorySize","","\/\/ 3. install macOS","let virtualMachine = VZVirtualMachine(configuration: configuration)","","let installer = VZMacOSInstaller(virtualMachine: virtualMachine, restoringFromImageAt: imageURL)","try await installer.install()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Using-your-Mac","text":"Using your Mac","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GPU acceleration ("},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization\/vzmacgraphicsdisplayconfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"built-in graphic device that exposes the GPU capabilities to the virtual Mac"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"you can run Metal in the virtual machine, and get great graphics performance in macOS","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["let graphicsConfiguration = VZMacGraphicsDeviceConfiguration()","graphicsConfiguration.displays = [","  VZMacGraphicsDisplayConfiguration(widthInPixels: 1920, heightInPixels: 1200, pixelsPerInch: 80)","  \/\/                                  üëÜüèª screen size and pixel density","]","","configuration.graphicsDevices = [graphicsConfiguration]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"virtual trackpad (","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization\/vzmactrackpadconfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"requires macOS 13 on both host OS and virtual machine","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["let trackpad = VZMacTrackpadConfiguration()","configuration.pointingDevices = [trackpad]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Sharing-files-between-host-OS-and-virtual-mac","text":"Sharing files between host OS and virtual mac","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"new in macOS 13 via Virtio file-system","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"you can choose which folders that you want to share with the virtual machine","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"any change you make from the host system is instantly reflected within the virtual machine and vice versa"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["\/\/                                              üëáüèª path to the directory we want to share","let sharedDirectory = VZSharedDirectory(url: directoryURL, readOnly: false)","let share = VZSingleDirectoryShare(directory: sharedDirectory) \/\/ can use VZMultipleDirectoryShare for more directories","","let tag = VZVirtioFileSystemDeviceConfiguration.macOSGuestAutomountTag \/\/ File system devices are identified by a tag","let sharingDevice = VZVirtioFileSystemDeviceConfiguration(tag: tag)","sharingDevice.share = share","","configuration.directorySharingDevices = [sharingDevice]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Linux","text":"Linux","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"anchor":"How-to-install-linux-into-a-vm","text":"How to install linux into a vm","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Three steps, like IRL:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"download image","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"put into a usb drive (as a device in the vm)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"run installer from usb drive","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"done via EFI boot loader"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"takes advantage of EFI boot discovery mechanism, which looks at each drive for one that can be booted","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"once detected, EFI will start the installer from the virtual usb drive"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["\/\/ 1. download image","","let diskImageURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"linux.iso\")","","\/\/ 2. put into a usb drive","","\/\/   üëáüèª A disk image attachment represents a piece of storage that we can attach to a device","let attachment = try! VZDiskImageStorageDeviceAttachment(url: diskImageURL, readOnly: true)","let usbDeviceConfiguration = VZUSBMassStorageDeviceConfiguration(attachment: attachment) \/\/ üëàüèª our usb drive","","configuration.storageDevices = [usbDeviceConfiguration, createBlockDevice()]","","\/\/ 3. run installer from usb drive","","let efi = VZEFIBootLoader()","\/\/ üëáüèª EFI requires this non-volatile memory to store information between boots","efi.variableStore = VZEFIVariableStore(creatingVariableStoreAt: storeURL, options: [])","configuration.bootLoader = efi \/\/ set EFI boot loader"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Running-your-vm","text":"Running your vm","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"graphics (Virtio GPU 2D)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let virtioGPU = VZVirtioGraphicsDeviceConfiguration()","virtioGPU.scanouts = [","  VZVirtioGraphicsScanoutConfiguration(widthInPixels: 1280, heightInPixels: 720) \/\/ üëàüèª virtual display","]","","configuration.graphicsDevices = [virtioGPU]"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Rosetta 2 (macOS Ventura)","anchor":"Rosetta-2-macOS-Ventura","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Linux binaries support"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"translates the Linux x86-64 binaries inside your virtual machine."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"useful when developing for x86-64 servers","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"vm setup:"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ setting up Rosetta","let rosettaDirectoryShare = try! VZLinuxRosettaDirectoryShare() \/\/ üëàüèª special object","let directorySharingDevice = VZVirtioFileSystemDeviceConfiguration(tag: \"RosettaShare\")","directorySharingDevice.share = rosettaDirectoryShare","","configuration.directorySharingDevices = [directorySharingDevice]"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"in the vm, run:"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"shell","code":["mount -t virtiofs RosettaShare \/mnt\/Rosetta","","sudo \/usr\/sbin\/update-binfmts --install rosetta \/mnt\/Rosetta\/rosetta \\","  --magic \"\\x7fELF\\x02\\x01\\x01\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x00\\x02\\x00\\x3e\\x00\" \\","  --mask \"\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xfe\\xfe\\x00\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xff\\xfe\\xff\\xff\\xff\" \\","  --credentials yes --preserve no --fix-binary yes"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"update-binfmts","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" tells the system to use Rosetta to handle any x86-64 binary"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"after running the commands above, every x86-64 binary launched will be translated by Rosetta."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Written By","anchor":"Written-By","level":2,"type":"hea